I think they want one of their own as chief dietician and researcher; and make it as an institution under Head office.

May be they want the institution to bring in international experts. I thought they already wanted international crate of diabetes after being told its division of Health and Medical services. What’s that mantra” we have it all in the home shore…” thing? So they must want their own and wait for national fleet after years of waiting. Or its just about Ugandan kind of protocol nonsense?

As a diabetic nurse have put it “if we are advanced here, whats gonna be you guys (in Uganda)? ”

Cholera, IF those are the actual facts about the cases, is man-made. I find it grossly incomprehensible that cholera that is very treatable could be followed by death in such a short space of time for a fully grown adult. With the available drugs, patients respond fast and well, most likely improving in 2 to 3 days. And they die in three days? It shows this is maltreatment of patients or worst case scenario criminal negligent case of doctors.
